---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How It Works | BeaconGuard Regulated AI Runtime Control"
  description="See how BeaconGuard validates request context, verifies trust conditions, applies deterministic controls, enforces ALLOW or DENY outcomes, and produces verifiable decision evidence before governed execution."
>
  <section>
    <h1>How It Works</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard evaluates enterprise requests before governed AI, APIs, or automated systems execute them. Each request passes through a deterministic runtime control boundary that validates context, verifies trust conditions, applies the active control set, enforces an explicit ALLOW or DENY result, and emits verifiable decision evidence.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <p class="section-label">Runtime sequence</p>
    <h2>Runtime Decision Sequence</h2>
    <p>
      Each request moves through six deterministic stages: request intake, validation, trust verification, control evaluation, enforcement, and evidence recording. The sequence completes before governed execution proceeds.
    </p>
    <figure class="runtime-sequence-section">
      <div
        class="runtime-sequence-scroll"
        tabindex="0"
        aria-label="Runtime decision sequence diagram; scroll horizontally to inspect"
      >
        <img
          src="/runtime-decision-sequence.svg"
          alt="BeaconGuard six-stage request lifecycle showing Request, Validate, Verify, Evaluate, Enforce, and Record, with ALLOW or DENY enforcement and verifiable decision evidence"
          class="runtime-sequence-img"
          width="1600"
          height="400"
          loading="eager"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </div>
      <p class="runtime-sequence-scroll-hint">
        Scroll horizontally to inspect the runtime sequence.
      </p>
      <figcaption class="runtime-sequence-caption">
        One request. Six deterministic stages. Evidence for every result.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Optional System Connector</h2>
    <p>
      Some enterprise applications do not natively produce the protocol or context structure required by the BeaconGuard runtime. The optional System Connector maps source protocols and context into the required request format before request validation.
    </p>
    <p>
      The System Connector does not evaluate controls, activate releases, or bypass enforcement.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Deterministic enforcement outcomes</h2>
    <h3>ALLOW</h3>
    <p>
      An allowed request satisfies the active control requirements and may proceed to governed execution.
    </p>
    <h3>DENY</h3>
    <p>
      A denied request is blocked before downstream execution. BeaconGuard fails closed when required validation, trust, freshness, replay, or control conditions are not satisfied.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Decision evidence and review</h2>
    <p>
      Every ALLOW or DENY result produces verifiable decision evidence containing the decision context, active release identity, control result, and outcome.
    </p>
    <p>
      Evidence may be routed for governance or human review without changing the runtime enforcement result that was already returned.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Technical Deepening</h2>
    <p>
      See <a href="/docs/architecture">System Architecture</a> for the complete control-plane, release-verification, activation, and runtime-boundary model.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/architecture">System Architecture</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/enforcement-runtime">Enforcement runtime</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/policy-model">Policy model</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/compliance-audit">Compliance and audit</a></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/deployment">Review deployment expectations</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/trust-assurance">Review Trust Center evidence surfaces</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .runtime-sequence-section {
      width: min(1440px, calc(100vw - 48px));
      max-width: none;
      margin: 3rem 0;
      margin-left: 50%;
      transform: translateX(-50%);
    }

    .runtime-sequence-scroll {
      width: 100%;
      overflow-x: auto;
      overflow-y: hidden;
      overscroll-behavior-inline: contain;
      scrollbar-gutter: stable;
      background: var(--bg-deep, #0b1220);
      border-radius: 8px;
    }

    .runtime-sequence-img {
      display: block;
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .runtime-sequence-scroll-hint {
      display: none;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--text-muted, #9aa8c0);
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
      padding-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }

    .runtime-sequence-caption {
      margin: 0.65rem 0 0;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      line-height: 1.45;
    }

    .runtime-sequence-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar {
      height: 8px;
    }

    .runtime-sequence-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
      background: var(--bg-deep, #0b1220);
      border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .runtime-sequence-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
      background: var(--border-muted, #2a3a5a);
      border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .runtime-sequence-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover {
      background: var(--accent-muted, #3a8a5a);
    }

    @media (max-width: 800px) {
      .runtime-sequence-section {
        width: calc(100vw - 24px);
      }

      .runtime-sequence-img {
        width: 900px;
        min-width: 900px;
      }

      .runtime-sequence-scroll-hint {
        display: block;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
